###FinancialForecast.java
package com.recursion;

public class FinancialForecast {

    // Recursive method to calculate future value
    public static double futureValue(double currentValue, double growthRate, int years) {

        if (years == 0) {
            return currentValue;
        }

        return futureValue(currentValue * (1 + growthRate), growthRate, years - 1);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        double currentValue = 10000;   // Initial investment
        double growthRate = 0.10;      // 10% annual growth
        int years = 5;

        double result = futureValue(currentValue, growthRate, years);

        System.out.printf("Future Value after %d years = %.2f%n", years, result);
    }
}



###Time Complexity

Time Complexity:O(n) (recursive call for each year)
Space Complexity:O(n) (recursive call stack)
Use Memoization to store previously computed results if the recursion has overlapping subproblems.
Use an Iterative approach to reduce space complexity from O(n) to O(1).
For compound growth, the formula Future Value = Present Value × (1 + r)^n computes the result directly in constant time using a power function.
